This article is a statement by the President on the 70th anniversary of V-E Day, which marks the victory of the Allied Forces over tyranny during World War II. The President pays tribute to the millions of lives lost during the war, including the six million Jews and others murdered by the Nazi regime. He also recognizes the sacrifices made by the more than 16 million Americans who served in World War II and the more than 400,000 Americans who gave their lives. The President reaffirms the commitment to defending liberty and human rights and honors the men and women in uniform who continue to protect the freedom that was won 70 years ago.